snippet.textDisplay:
I saw American Beauty for the first time this year. I'm from a small town in Scotland and I watched the film in Tampa, Florida with my beloved American sweetheart. It was such a profoundly moving film. I was really affected by Spacey's performance. In fact, I enjoyed him in Swimming with Sharks, K-Pax, 21... everything really. I am a fan of his work. But aye, American Beauty was something. As Burnham narrated from the point of death, it was kinda like Spacey narrating. The themes of the film fit with the issues of the day: sexuality, sexual impulse, etc.

It would appear the man had a rather severe childhood due to a deeply troubled father. If I'm not mistaken Kevin hasn't actually ever been accused of raping anyone, right? The allegations are fondling? I mean, that's not great but these are weaker ripples or lesser evils than were visited upon Kevin. Still, not good accusations.

Ultimately, I imagine Kevin has a bit stone heart just from sheer trauma and survival mechanics and while it's not our place to judge as an audience we do get offended by such reports. Forgiveness is foundational to my particular moral code. I suspect the dude could really reel his shit in but I don't think he's the devil incarnate.

I love the performances, I understand the impact of adverse childhood experiences, I loathe the fact he may have hurt others but ultimately we all hurt people in some fashion but far less publicly. I would hope for healing and forgiveness to prevail where it can.
